Use `OnSleep` / `OnResume` in your `App` class with `Preferences` for lightweight persistence:

**App.xaml.cs**
```csharp
public partial class App : Application
{
    public App()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        MainPage = new NavigationPage(new NotePage());
    }

    protected override void OnSleep()
    {
        // Fire an event so pages can save state
        MessagingCenter.Send(this, "AppSleep");
    }

    protected override void OnResume()
    {
        MessagingCenter.Send(this, "AppResume");
    }
}
```

**NotePage.xaml.cs**
```csharp
public partial class NotePage : ContentPage
{
    private const string DraftKey = "note_draft";

    public NotePage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();

        // Restore any saved draft on creation
        if (Preferences.ContainsKey(DraftKey))
            NoteEditor.Text = Preferences.Get(DraftKey, string.Empty);

        MessagingCenter.Subscribe<App>(this, "AppSleep", _ => SaveDraft());
        MessagingCenter.Subscribe<App>(this, "AppResume", _ => RestoreDraft());
    }

    private void SaveDraft()
    {
        Preferences.Set(DraftKey, NoteEditor.Text ?? string.Empty);
    }

    private void RestoreDraft()
    {
        NoteEditor.Text = Preferences.Get(DraftKey, string.Empty);
    }

    public void ClearDraft()
    {
        Preferences.Remove(DraftKey);
    }

    protected override void OnDisappearing()
    {
        base.OnDisappearing();
        MessagingCenter.Unsubscribe<App>(this, "AppSleep");
        MessagingCenter.Unsubscribe<App>(this, "AppResume");
    }
}
```

**NotePage.xaml** (relevant snippet)
```xml
<Editor x:Name="NoteEditor"
        Placeholder="Start typing your note..." />
```

### How it works

| Lifecycle event | What happens |
|---|---|
| **`OnSleep`** | App backgrounds → draft saved to `Preferences` |
| **`OnResume`** | App foregrounds → draft restored from `Preferences` |
| **Page created** | Any previously saved draft is loaded |
| **Note submitted** | Call `ClearDraft()` to remove stale data |

### Tips
- **`Preferences`** stores small strings via platform-native storage (NSUserDefaults / SharedPreferences). For large notes, use `File.WriteAllTextAsync` to a path from `FileSystem.AppDataDirectory` instead.
- **`MessagingCenter`** is deprecated in .NET 8+. If targeting newer MAUI, use the `WeakReferenceMessenger` from the **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** NuGet package — same pattern, just swap `MessagingCenter` for `WeakReferenceMessenger.Default`.
